        "id": 3956518,
        "name": "David Bueker",
        "username": "David_Bu3ker",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/david_bu3ker/{size}/319725_2.png",
        "created_at": "2022-12-22T16:09:39.655Z",
        "cooked": "<p><a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/note.asp?iWine=3330866&amp;iNote=10211223\"><b>2018 Yves Boyer-Martenot Meursault Les Narvaux</b></a> - France, Burgundy, C\u00f4te de Beaune, Meursault (12/14/2022)<br>\nProbably too early but with only the one bottle there was no \u201cgood\u201d time to open this. Overall I enjoyed the ripe stone fruit and spice core of the wine. It could have done with a touch more freshness, but I suspect that was more a vintage issue than anything else, and wineries don\u2019t control the weather. With a citrus-sauced chicken dish it made a fine pairing, so the important job of accompanying a meal was well satisfied. Not sure whether I would buy is again, though I suspect I would like to try it in a brighter vintage if there ever is such a thing again.</p>",
